This paper deals with video activity understanding and transfer learning, which are topics commonly found in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The use of meta-learning is also a key aspect of the paper, which suggests a possible fit with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper deals with first-person action recognition, which is a topic that can be relevant to robotics (cs.RO) research. Finally, the paper deals with visual cues and public datasets, which suggests a possible fit with multimedia (cs.MM) research.
